storm.starter
Class TransactionalGlobalCount

java.lang.Object
  storm.starter.TransactionalGlobalCount

public class TransactionalGlobalCount
extends Object

This is a basic example of a transactional topology. It keeps a count of the number of tuples seen so far in a database. The source of data and the databases are mocked out as in memory maps for demonstration purposes. This class is defined in depth on the wiki at https://github.com/nathanmarz/storm/wiki/Transactional-topologies
